Từ điển Anh - Việt
 ■Xem arcanum

Anh - Anh
arcana
[α:'keɪnə]
■ plural noun [treated as sing. or plural] (sing. arcanum)
1》 secrets; mysteries.
2》 either of the two groups of cards in a tarot pack: the twenty-two trumps (the major arcana) and the fifty-six suit cards (the minor arcana).
Origin
C16: from L., neut. plural of arcanus (see arcane).

sentences.en: They don't know the arcana of U. S. immigration law.
